This section contains the contents of the repository's files.# CodeGraph data files — local to each machine, not for committing.
# Ignore everything in .codegraph/ except this file itself, so transient
# files (the database, daemon.pid, sockets, logs) never show up in git.
*
!.gitignore# Business Model: FORGE

## Revenue Streams
1. **Marketplace Commission:** 15% fee on every successful transaction.
2. **FORGE Pro (Subscription):** $29/mo for sellers to get higher search priority, lowered 5% commission, and "Verified Builder" status.
3. **Enterprise Whitelabel:** License the FORGE infrastructure to companies for internal "Agentic Asset Stores."

## Payout Structure
* **Seller Share:** 85% of transaction value.
* **Platform Share:** 15% (Covers hosting, Stripe fees, and verification compute).

## Growth Loops
* **The "Built with FORGE" Watermark:** Every landing page sold includes a tiny badge linking back to the marketplace.
* **Creator Ecosystem:** Incentivizing YouTube/X "Vibe Coders" to list their tutorial assets on FORGE for their audience.

## Key Metrics (KPIs)
* **GMV (Gross Merchandise Volume):** Total volume of assets traded.
* **Verification Pass Rate:** Percentage of assets that successfully clear our AI Sandbox.
* **Seller Retention:** Percentage of builders who list 3+ items.# Competitor Map: FORGE (Vs. The Status Quo 2026)

| Competitor       | URL                 | Pricing         | Strengths                      | Weaknesses                                   | The FORGE Gap                     |
|------------------|---------------------|-----------------|--------------------------------|----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| **PromptBase**   | promptbase.com      | 20% Commission  | First to market, high traffic. | Only supports text prompts. No code/apps.    | FORGE supports full apps/workflow.|
| **Gumroad**      | gumroad.com         | 10% Flat Fee    | Massive creator trust base.    | No technical validation or AI sandboxing.    | FORGE "Verifies" the code works.  |
| **Fiverr (AI)**  | fiverr.com/ai       | Service-based   | Professional freelancer talent.| No instant asset downloads. Slower.         | FORGE is a product-first "Click-Buy-Use"|
| **n8n Templates**| n8n.io/templates    | Free / Open     | Native workflow support.       | Not a monetization tool for developers.      | FORGE lets developers sell these. |
| **Replit**       | replit.com          | Pro Subs        | Integrated dev environment.    | No cross-platform marketplace for sale.      | FORGE assets work anywhere.       |

## The FORGE Unfair Advantage
**Technical Sandboxing & "Vibe Logic" Verification.**  
While other platforms sell files, FORGE sells "Verified Functionality." We use an automated agent to test every listing (workflows, code, apps) to ensure it runs as described. This creates a high-trust layer for the "vibe coder" economy.<!DOCTYPE html>
